  "text": "Experiments were carried out in a stirred batch reactor of 500 cm [CITATION_1] volume. This reactor was provided with temperature and speed control, and immersed in a thermostatic bath capable of maintaining the reaction temperature to within ±0.1°C by means of an electrical device connected to a PID controller. The impeller speed between 500 and 1200 rpm were tested; a stirring speed of 600 rpm was found appropriate to avoid external mass transfer limitation [CITATION_2] .",
